FBIS4-33583 "drlat110_m_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-110 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 Brazil Colombian Cartels' Top Man in Brazil Escapes Again Colombian Cartels' Top Man in Brazil Escapes Again PY0706142894 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 1000 GMT 7 Jun 94 PY0706142894 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network Portuguese BFN [Text] Antonio Mota Graca, aka Curica, who was responsible for the transportation of the 7 metric tons of cocaine seized in Tocantins State, is the most important man from the Colombian cartels in Brazil. Although 13 drug traffickers have been arrested, Curica again escaped Federal Police. In 1991, he was freed from inside a Military Police patrol car when he was leaving jail to testify before the court in Itapecirica da Serra, Sao Paulo State.
